      <section eId="section_9">
        <heading><b>Annex B – Territorial extent and application in the United Kingdom</b></heading>
        <paragraph>
          <num>81 </num>
          <content>
            <p>The provisions in this Act form part of the law of England, Wales, Northern Ireland and Scotland. The Act extends to the UK apart from activity relating to devolved matters in Scotland. Subject to that, the Act will apply UK-wide.</p>
            <table uk:widths="1.24in 1.12in 1.12in 1.12in 1.53in">
              <tr>
                <th>
                  <p><b>Provision</b></p>
                </th>
                <th>
                  <p><b>Extends to E &amp; W and applies to England?</b></p>
                </th>
                <th>
                  <p><b>Extends to E &amp; W and applies to Wales?</b></p>
                </th>
                <th>
                  <p><b>Extends and applies to Scotland?</b></p>
                </th>
                <th>
                  <p><b>Extends and applies to Northern Ireland?</b></p>
                </th>
              </tr>
